- Yeah, yeah.

01:12.363 --> 01:13.363
You okay, buddy?

01:13.865 --> 01:16.534
- I think so. It's just a lot.
- Yeah.

01:17.243 --> 01:18.912
Yeah. Well, let's get you home.

01:22.999 --> 01:25.126
Did you find any, like, clues or whatever?

01:26.169 --> 01:27.670
Well, I mean, you know,

01:27.754 --> 01:30.131
we try to put together
everything we can, but...

01:31.382 --> 01:33.843
you don't know what the clues are
until you know the crime.

01:39.432 --> 01:42.018
Plenty of boys think
there's not much choice at all.

01:43.103 --> 01:44.395
They have to be strong...

01:46.314 --> 01:47.315
<i>...and stoic...</i>

01:49.192 --> 01:51.319
<i>♪ Come closer and see ♪</i>

01:52.195 --> 01:54.531
<i>♪ See into the dark ♪</i>

01:55.156 --> 01:57.450
<i>♪ Just follow your eyes ♪</i>

01:58.118 --> 02:00.954
<i>♪ Just follow your eyes ♪</i>

02:01.037 --> 02:02.997
<i>♪ Suddenly I stop ♪</i>

02:03.832 --> 02:05.500
<i>♪ But I know it's too late ♪</i>

02:05.625 --> 02:06.709
...and in control.

02:07.210 --> 02:08.461
<i>♪ I'm lost in a forest ♪</i>

02:08.586 --> 02:09.838
<i>They have to be a man.</i>

02:12.924 --> 02:15.051
<i>♪ The girl was never there ♪</i>

02:16.511 --> 02:18.805
<i>And hide the things
that hurt the most.</i>

02:18.930 --> 02:21.474
<i>♪ I'm running towards nothing ♪</i>

02:21.766 --> 02:24.894
<i>♪ Again and again and again ♪</i>

02:28.773 --> 02:29.773
Yeah?

02:33.236 --> 02:35.488
<i>What happens
when they can't hide anymore?</i>

02:46.749 --> 02:47.749
Hello?

02:49.711 --> 02:50.837
Hello, Sheriff.

02:54.340 --> 02:55.884
And where did you find it?

02:59.637 --> 03:00.637
I see.

03:02.724 --> 03:05.518
No. No, I don't know the place.
He never mentioned it.

03:09.772 --> 03:10.773
I understand.

03:11.816 --> 03:13.193
Yes, that's fine.

03:17.864 --> 03:19.157
I don't know, um...

03:19.699 --> 03:24.579
I know my son did drugs on occasion,
but I never saw steroids.

03:33.046 --> 03:35.006
You haven't mentioned if...

03:36.633 --> 03:38.551
there was evidence he was harmed.

03:52.440 --> 03:54.025
That boy Clay Jensen...

03:54.943 --> 03:56.611
you'll talk to him again, I hope?

03:59.322 --> 04:00.323
Thank you, Sheriff.

04:00.823 --> 04:03.701
Hey! Keep your mind on the medicine.

04:04.452 --> 04:05.453
Yes, Mum.

04:06.913 --> 04:10.333
Keep your head down,
and leave this woman to her grief.

04:15.380 --> 04:17.048
- Amara Josephine?
- Yes?

04:17.839 --> 04:19.926
They found blood on the ground.

04:20.426 --> 04:21.928
Oh, no. Upstairs.

04:23.554 --> 04:24.973
Someone hurt my son.

04:25.807 --> 04:26.891
Oh, dear God.

04:45.159 --> 04:48.371
We both know that's where
this whole story begins and ends.

04:49.247 --> 04:51.040
<i>With boys trying to be men.</i>

04:51.708 --> 04:53.626
<i>And everyone they hurt along the way.</i>

04:55.336 --> 04:56.546
<i>Everyone they hurt.</i>

04:58.214 --> 04:59.882
<i>Including their own damn selves.</i>

05:06.514 --> 05:07.514
Fuck!

05:09.225 --> 05:10.226
Fuck!

05:13.855 --> 05:15.523
Hey, Jess...

05:18.026 --> 05:19.569
Justin, they found Bryce's...

05:22.113 --> 05:24.532
What the hell?

05:25.283 --> 05:29.078
Uh, it's Jess.
Jess has just... she lost an earring.

05:31.622 --> 05:33.249
- Yeah...
- Justin, what the fuck?

05:37.170 --> 05:40.089
Uh, I... I'll call you back, okay?

05:40.798 --> 05:42.759
I thought you got rid of it last night.

05:44.469 --> 05:47.263
First guy didn't work out, okay?
I will... I got it.

05:47.347 --> 05:51.601
- You can't just leave it lying around!
- Just chill. I got it.

05:54.145 --> 05:56.522
They found his Range Rover
and blood on the ground.

05:56.606 --> 05:57.815
They're calling it a homicide.

06:00.902 --> 06:02.945
- Fuck!
- They found drugs

06:03.029 --> 06:04.029
and...

06:04.447 --> 06:06.074
- fingerprints.
- Drugs? What...

06:07.241 --> 06:08.409
What drugs?

06:08.493 --> 06:11.204
She didn't say, but they found
fingerprints that weren't his.

06:11.871 --> 06:12.872
Okay, well...

06:15.792 --> 06:16.876
That's all right, right?

06:17.460 --> 06:18.461
It's a car.

06:19.045 --> 06:20.671
It's got a ton of fingerprints.

06:20.755 --> 06:22.595
He probably drove
his Hillcrest friends around.

06:22.632 --> 06:24.425
Justin, my prints could be on it.

06:25.051 --> 06:26.052
Did you kill him?

06:26.761 --> 06:27.595
Of course not.

06:27.678 --> 06:28.930
Then don't worry about it.

06:32.016 --> 06:33.016
You don't...

06:34.227 --> 06:36.267
You don't want to know
why my prints could be on it?

06:36.687 --> 06:39.065
No, I really don't.

06:54.956 --> 06:56.457
How are you feeling today, Dad?

06:58.042 --> 07:00.628
Amara Josephine says
you've not much of an appetite.

07:00.711 --> 07:04.799
It's those West Indies spices
she puts in everything.

07:05.007 --> 07:06.134
She's Kenyan, Dad,

07:06.926 --> 07:08.052
by way of the UK.

07:09.554 --> 07:12.515
And I don't think she puts anything
in your scrambled eggs.

07:13.224 --> 07:14.225
Where's the boy?

07:16.310 --> 07:18.438
He hasn't been in to see me for days.

07:19.230 --> 07:20.230
He's...

07:22.900 --> 07:23.900
with friends...

07:25.027 --> 07:26.027
for a few days.

07:26.779 --> 07:29.490
Off drinking
and causing trouble.

07:30.158 --> 07:31.158
Good for him.

07:32.243 --> 07:34.954
Boys need to blow off steam.

07:35.746 --> 07:40.418
You're too hard on the kid.
Boys need their wild time.

07:41.794 --> 07:42.795
Yes, Dad.

07:44.505 --> 07:46.841
It's how they grow up to be men.

07:50.261 --> 07:51.261
Yes.

07:51.929 --> 07:54.640
I remember being young in this house,

07:55.391 --> 07:57.518
raising holy hell.

07:58.853 --> 08:00.938
Give him room, for Christ's sakes.

08:01.314 --> 08:04.609
Let him make his fucking mistakes,
he's a boy.

08:05.234 --> 08:06.235
Yes, Dad.

08:07.361 --> 08:10.072
The new painkillers are for shit,
by the way.

08:10.156 --> 08:11.908
That doctor doesn't have a clue.

08:11.991 --> 08:15.578
Goddamn witch doctors,
all of ‘em, there’s no science...

08:17.705 --> 08:20.833
<i>You found steroids
in the Range Rover in quantity.</i>

08:22.210 --> 08:24.545
<i>You thought: "Drug deal gone bad."</i>

08:25.588 --> 08:26.588
<i>Makes sense.</i>

08:26.631 --> 08:28.299
You know, you can't just do this.

08:28.382 --> 08:29.902
What about our First Amendment rights?

08:31.177 --> 08:34.847
Yeah, that would be the Fourth Amendment,
Mr. de la Cruz. And the Supreme Court

08:34.931 --> 08:39.143
has established our school's right
to function <i>in loco parentis.</i>

08:40.436 --> 08:42.938
Dempsey, what the hell?
You got nothing to say about this?

08:43.022 --> 08:45.816
We talked about it in pre-season.
Liberty Tigers play clean.

08:45.900 --> 08:47.276
I say go ahead and search.

08:50.530 --> 08:51.572
This yours, Justin?

08:53.241 --> 08:54.241
Uh, yes, sir.

09:01.499 --> 09:02.499
Sheriff?

09:03.376 --> 09:04.418
Yeah?

09:08.506 --> 09:09.507
Take a look.

09:10.633 --> 09:14.053
<i>Quite a few of the guys
at Liberty were using, it turns out.</i>

09:15.346 --> 09:18.641
<i>And you can draw a line
from every one of them to Bryce Walker.</i>

09:22.979 --> 09:24.480
Holliday?

09:24.564 --> 09:25.564
Yes, sir?

09:28.067 --> 09:29.443
Come with me, son.

09:32.446 --> 09:34.907
<i>One of those lines is brighter
than the others.</i>

09:35.825 --> 09:36.951
<i>And I'll tell you why.</i>

09:39.453 --> 09:40.663
Hey, Dad. What's up?

09:42.081 --> 09:44.875
Just doing some business, buddy.
Nothing to worry about.

09:47.503 --> 09:48.504
Fuck.

09:48.921 --> 09:50.923
Hey. Do you guys know what's going on?

09:51.132 --> 09:53.342
They searched
the football lockers this morning,

09:53.426 --> 09:55.052
- Caught Luke with juice.
- Luke?

09:55.803 --> 09:58.003
You want to tell me
where you got the steroids?

10:00.516 --> 10:01.851
How long you been juicing?

10:02.018 --> 10:04.770
Do you know
if anyone else on the team is on steroids?

10:04.854 --> 10:06.856
No, sir. No.
I didn't even know about Luke.

10:06.939 --> 10:08.065
Do you know of anyone else

10:08.149 --> 10:11.068
who might have been
still talking to Bryce Walker?

10:12.820 --> 10:13.821
No, sir.

10:13.988 --> 10:16.174
You're gonna protest his funeral?
I mean, Jess, come on.

10:16.198 --> 10:17.408
This is so fucked up.

10:17.491 --> 10:18.784
This wasn't me!

10:19.994 --> 10:23.331
You guys, heads up if you have shit
in your lockers. They're doing a search.

10:23.414 --> 10:25.094
Yeah, they already did, the football team.

10:25.124 --> 10:27.644
No, my dad's still here.
They'll do the whole school, I promise.

10:27.668 --> 10:30.338
- Well, I've got nothing to hide.
- Well, good for you.

10:32.632 --> 10:35.009
Why does he give a shit
about a locker search?

10:35.092 --> 10:36.344
So, you and Bryce,

10:36.969 --> 10:38.054
you weren't in touch?

10:39.889 --> 10:42.475
Homecoming was the first time I saw him
since he left Liberty.

10:42.558 --> 10:44.185
So, you didn't know he was dealing?

10:44.518 --> 10:46.538
- I didn't.
- You bought from Bryce Walker?

10:46.562 --> 10:48.397
- No, sir.
- You didn't?

10:49.065 --> 10:50.065
Then who?

10:52.026 --> 10:53.861
Son, this is a murder investigation.

10:53.944 --> 10:55.905
If you didn't buy
from the kid who was killed,

10:55.988 --> 10:57.907
I need to know who you got them from.

11:03.204 --> 11:04.204
Tim Pozzi.

11:05.122 --> 11:06.916
He works out at City Gym.

11:07.667 --> 11:08.918
In the warehouse district.

11:09.251 --> 11:10.836
<i>It's not just athletes.</i>

11:10.920 --> 11:14.632
Okay? I've known kids, all kinds of kids,
that juice. It's...

11:15.216 --> 11:16.216
a body thing.

11:16.258 --> 11:18.302
What kids? Who?

11:19.345 --> 11:20.345
I mean...

11:22.098 --> 11:24.141
I can't think of any names...

11:24.725 --> 11:25.893
off the top of my head.

11:55.965 --> 11:57.675
I don't believe it. Not Alex.

12:03.097 --> 12:05.599
"Testosterone cypionate."

12:05.683 --> 12:06.684
Steroids.

12:07.518 --> 12:08.518
Bryce was dealing them.

12:09.520 --> 12:11.897
Why would Bryce deal?
He didn't need the money.

12:11.981 --> 12:13.399
Maybe it was about control.

12:14.066 --> 12:15.693
Anyone who bought from him,

12:15.776 --> 12:16.944
he had a hand on them.

12:17.236 --> 12:19.321
But Alex, he's a mellow guy.

12:19.572 --> 12:20.990
Alex is mellow?

12:28.622 --> 12:31.083
- They're searching lockers today.
- Good.

12:31.667 --> 12:32.877
Find a lot of those.

12:33.043 --> 12:35.045
Wait, they told me
that you wanted to do this.

12:35.379 --> 12:37.798
We don't need her permission.
The group decided.

12:37.882 --> 12:39.884
The group did not decide, you decided.

12:40.134 --> 12:41.886
You just want to piss people off.

12:41.969 --> 12:44.513
Yes, I fucking do.
People should be pissed off!

12:44.597 --> 12:47.117
This doesn't end 'cause
they put a fucking rapist in the ground.

12:47.183 --> 12:49.310
My rapist! My rapist, okay?

12:50.060 --> 12:51.687
And I say we can't do this.

12:51.771 --> 12:54.023
We can't be this!

12:54.106 --> 12:55.666
'Cause you want to protect your rapist,

12:55.733 --> 12:58.569
- and that's messed up.
- No, because there's human decency!

13:01.238 --> 13:02.698
I think I understand.

13:05.159 --> 13:06.327
You're still a victim.

13:07.912 --> 13:11.665
Well, you'll know where to find
the survivors on Sunday.

13:17.129 --> 13:18.589
<i>This is fucked up.</i>

13:19.340 --> 13:21.175
This is like an invasion of privacy.

13:21.258 --> 13:22.968
He got it out of a garbage can.

13:23.052 --> 13:24.053
Fuck Justin!

13:24.136 --> 13:27.181
He's gonna rat people out about drugs?
Really?

13:27.807 --> 13:28.807
Are you...

13:29.642 --> 13:30.642
Are you okay?

13:30.684 --> 13:31.684
Are you?

13:31.936 --> 13:33.813
Are you okay? Ani, are you?

13:34.688 --> 13:35.689
Fuck you guys!

13:42.112 --> 13:43.112
Alex...

13:43.322 --> 13:45.908
Just... just don't tell my dad, okay?

13:46.742 --> 13:47.910
Is it about Bryce?

13:47.993 --> 13:48.993
No.

13:50.287 --> 13:51.997
I didn't buy from Bryce.

13:52.581 --> 13:54.625
Luke hooked me up with a guy.

13:55.626 --> 13:57.294
But why?

13:57.378 --> 13:58.546
Why do you think?

13:59.463 --> 14:00.756
Just look at me.

14:01.757 --> 14:04.635
I think you're very handsome.
I think you're adorable.

14:04.844 --> 14:07.263
Yeah. Well, you're the one girl
in this county

14:07.346 --> 14:09.181
that would go for a skinny, sad kid.

14:09.348 --> 14:10.808
And you went for Clay, so...

14:11.684 --> 14:13.644
I'm gonna let that go
because you're under stress.

14:13.978 --> 14:16.605
Wouldn't you have done anything
to have Hannah love you back?

14:17.439 --> 14:20.860
To choose you over Zach,
or stupid Justin?

14:22.069 --> 14:26.073
Even before I shot myself,
it's like the pieces never worked.

14:27.199 --> 14:28.659
And they're never going to.

14:37.585 --> 14:38.586
<i>The quiet boy.</i>

14:39.920 --> 14:40.921
<i>The gentle one.</i>

14:43.215 --> 14:45.092
<i>There's more going on than you know.</i>

14:45.801 --> 14:48.053
<i>But I don't have to tell you that, do I?</i>

14:55.644 --> 14:56.687
- Hey.
- Hey.

15:02.151 --> 15:03.193
I finished.

15:03.444 --> 15:06.405
This is the last drink on the menu
including the seasonal specials.

15:06.864 --> 15:08.157
Wow, that's...

15:09.033 --> 15:10.367
- Congratulations.
- Thank you.

15:10.451 --> 15:12.453
Yes, it's been quite the odyssey.

15:12.536 --> 15:13.536
Yeah.

15:15.748 --> 15:16.749
You want to sit?

15:17.124 --> 15:20.544
I mean, we can be the kind of friends
that drink coffee, right?

15:21.128 --> 15:23.047
- I think we can be that.
- Yeah.

15:23.130 --> 15:26.300
Our friendship survived
you dumping me for Justin before, so...

15:27.801 --> 15:28.886
That was a joke.

15:30.554 --> 15:31.430
I'm sorry.

15:31.513 --> 15:33.265
Let's talk about anything else.

15:35.643 --> 15:37.144
Can I just ask you one question?

15:38.354 --> 15:40.814
What is it about me
that isn't good enough?

15:41.690 --> 15:43.484
Alex, come on. It's not...

15:44.318 --> 15:45.486
It's not about that.

15:45.569 --> 15:48.030
Then what? 'Cause I don't understand

15:48.113 --> 15:51.200
why you weren't ready to date me
but you're ready to date him.

15:51.283 --> 15:54.036
Why you want to be with one person
and not someone else,

15:54.119 --> 15:55.287
you can't always explain it.

15:56.121 --> 15:57.121
Well, try.

16:00.918 --> 16:01.919
It's like...

16:02.503 --> 16:04.463
you learn to listen to your body.

16:05.965 --> 16:07.174
Who you're attracted to.

16:09.301 --> 16:10.469
Who makes you feel safe.

16:10.970 --> 16:11.971
Safe?

16:12.930 --> 16:14.390
He let his best friend rape you!

16:14.473 --> 16:17.309
And then he lied to you about it!
How the fuck does that feel safe?

16:20.813 --> 16:21.897
You should probably go.

16:22.940 --> 16:24.024
Right, yeah.

16:25.776 --> 16:26.860
- Shit!
- Jess!

16:27.152 --> 16:30.823
- I'm so sorry! I'll get napkins.
- God!

16:33.534 --> 16:35.786
- You okay?
- Yeah. Thanks.

16:44.461 --> 16:45.713
<i>Sooner or later,</i>

16:46.338 --> 16:48.173
<i>what's hidden comes out.</i>

16:55.556 --> 16:56.557
<i>Sooner or later,</i>

16:57.016 --> 16:58.100
<i>enough is enough.</i>

17:07.943 --> 17:11.946
So for now, just gonna have to do the bar,
make sure you have proper form.

17:14.074 --> 17:17.994
And then, after a couple of sessions,
maybe we'll add a little bit more weight.

17:18.078 --> 17:19.663
I can do more weight than this.

17:21.248 --> 17:22.248
Well...

17:23.500 --> 17:25.252
let's just see how this goes first.

17:25.627 --> 17:27.546
Oh, don't start yet. Forgot something.

17:31.717 --> 17:34.344
Hey, if you want some shit
to get you started, let me know.

17:35.387 --> 17:38.891
- Okay.
- Dude, no shame. Everyone needs help.

17:39.266 --> 17:41.393
Come see me later, and don't tell Dempsey.

17:43.270 --> 17:44.646
All right, here we go.

17:47.024 --> 17:48.344
Don't want you to hurt your back.

17:48.400 --> 17:50.110
- Yeah, awesome. Thanks.
- Yeah.

17:53.781 --> 17:56.033
<i>♪ They got sick of the boys club ♪</i>

17:56.533 --> 17:58.869
<i>♪ They got sick of those men ♪</i>

17:59.578 --> 18:04.374
<i>♪ Tellin' them what they couldn't do
'Cause they were too shy or too femme ♪</i>

18:05.751 --> 18:07.920
<i>♪ Until they thought of their own space ♪</i>

18:08.754 --> 18:10.756
<i>♪ Where they could plug in that tight ♪</i>

18:12.049 --> 18:14.259
They clean out the gym lockers
at the end of summer,

18:14.343 --> 18:16.261
so keep these in your main locker.

18:16.762 --> 18:19.973
- In summer, I don't have a locker.
- Use the one from last year.

18:20.057 --> 18:23.685
They lost the master key,
so no searching, no new combos.

18:24.144 --> 18:25.604
All right, got it. Thanks.

18:30.359 --> 18:32.361
<i>The steroids led us to Alex...</i>

18:34.446 --> 18:35.989
<i>but he didn't buy from Bryce.</i>

18:37.199 --> 18:38.826
- Hey, Alex. What's up?
- Hey!

18:39.535 --> 18:42.579
Just working out and then
I just wandered over here. How about you?

18:42.663 --> 18:45.749
Math! I mean, math! Come on, let's go.

18:45.833 --> 18:48.418
- No one uses it!
- Picking him up from Summer School.

18:48.961 --> 18:51.338
I feel you, man.
My brother's an asshole, too.

18:51.421 --> 18:52.422
Yeah. See you, man.

18:52.923 --> 18:55.008
<i>Who else showed signs
of steroid use?</i>

18:56.635 --> 18:58.887
<i>Violent mood swings. Aggression.</i>

19:02.182 --> 19:03.517
<i>Montgomery de la Cruz.</i>

19:12.943 --> 19:16.196
The police took Luke,
but he didn't buy from Bryce.

19:16.947 --> 19:17.990
And Monty did.

19:28.208 --> 19:29.543
He's clearing out.

19:32.838 --> 19:36.008
<i>I hate to admit
Alex and Monty had anything in common...</i>

19:37.426 --> 19:39.386
<i>and Alex would hate me for saying so...</i>

19:40.846 --> 19:43.974
<i>but it turns out they had way more
in common than we thought.</i>

20:13.921 --> 20:17.132
Wait. What do you think
Monty doesn't want Winston talking about?

20:22.763 --> 20:23.889
This was on the seat.

20:25.933 --> 20:27.517
