45:15.379 --> 45:17.131
Dude, it's the wrong fucking house!

45:18.632 --> 45:19.633
Oh, shit!

45:28.058 --> 45:31.186
No! No! Hey! Hey. It's fine.

45:31.270 --> 45:32.604
Speak and you die.

45:32.688 --> 45:35.107
What the fuck is wrong with you?

45:38.527 --> 45:40.696
No, no! It's okay. You're fine.

46:06.180 --> 46:08.974
Oh, that was some fucked-up shit!

46:10.017 --> 46:12.519
Oh, fuck it, man!
I can't believe we just did that.

46:14.772 --> 46:15.773
Oh...

46:21.779 --> 46:23.489
You're a horrible person.

46:24.823 --> 46:25.991
Yeah, pretty much.

46:26.742 --> 46:28.827
That kid is scarred for life
because of us.

46:28.911 --> 46:32.790
Alex. Baby, we're all scarred for life.
Check your fucking head.

46:33.540 --> 46:35.876
- I don't ever want to see you again.
- What?

46:36.126 --> 46:37.669
Alex, come on.

46:38.462 --> 46:39.463
Come back.

46:40.297 --> 46:41.297
Alex!

46:44.718 --> 46:46.762
Where are you gonna get your shit from,
sweetheart?

46:46.887 --> 46:48.806
Only friends and family get the discount.

46:50.682 --> 46:51.682
Alex!

46:57.773 --> 46:59.358
It's good to see you again.

47:00.734 --> 47:02.402
What's your pleasure today, honey?

47:08.033 --> 47:09.033
Sweetie...

47:14.706 --> 47:15.707
Come here.

47:17.501 --> 47:19.419
Come here. It's okay.

47:24.174 --> 47:25.217
It's gonna be okay.

47:26.051 --> 47:28.679
<i>I don't think
I'll ever forget that little kid's face.</i>

47:29.972 --> 47:31.515
I'm sure he won't forget mine.

47:33.433 --> 47:36.854
After that, I didn't get the discount,
which is why the payments went up.

47:37.396 --> 47:41.066
He never blackmailed me.
He never said a thing about anything.

47:41.149 --> 47:42.234
Wait, so are you...

47:43.110 --> 47:44.987
Are you using now, or are you clean?

47:45.863 --> 47:46.905
Nobody's clean.

47:48.407 --> 47:51.493
- Alex, you don't have to go.
- Yeah. Well, I'm not going to stay.

47:52.327 --> 47:53.495
I don't want you to...

47:56.582 --> 47:57.942
I don't want you to hurt yourself.

47:59.001 --> 48:00.961
Yeah, I've run out of ways to do that.

48:18.604 --> 48:20.355
Do you think I'm a sad, skinny kid?

48:24.026 --> 48:25.068
Ah...

48:25.652 --> 48:28.488
I think you are a lean...

48:29.823 --> 48:32.284
but right-sized...

48:33.452 --> 48:34.661
very handsome,

48:35.454 --> 48:36.788
very complicated kid.

48:42.711 --> 48:43.712
I'll take it.

48:54.139 --> 48:55.807
How's... how's Alex?

48:58.352 --> 48:59.353
Messed up.

49:01.188 --> 49:02.272
But aren't we all?

49:04.066 --> 49:07.778
You know, I really didn't think
he had anything to do with Bryce, but...

49:10.572 --> 49:13.241
drugs of any kind, man, they fuck you up.

49:14.034 --> 49:15.034
Yeah.

49:18.747 --> 49:22.084
I'll have you know,
the gun is gone for good.

49:25.212 --> 49:26.713
Awesome. Thanks.

49:30.884 --> 49:32.511
You seem awfully dark tonight.

49:35.347 --> 49:36.431
How are you not?

49:39.851 --> 49:40.852
I guess I am.

49:43.480 --> 49:46.316
But I'm alive,
so I figure I'm ahead of the game.

49:49.277 --> 49:50.277
Right.

49:52.739 --> 49:55.534
I don't want to believe
someone we know killed Bryce.

49:57.244 --> 49:59.663
But it seems like
everyone we know had a reason.

50:00.747 --> 50:02.165
Everyone's got their shit.

50:07.004 --> 50:08.004
Yes.

50:10.799 --> 50:15.637
<i>♪ Jesus Christ I'm so blue all the time ♪</i>

50:16.054 --> 50:19.558
<i>♪ And that's just how I feel ♪</i>

50:19.641 --> 50:25.981
<i>♪ Always have and I always will ♪</i>

50:26.481 --> 50:30.277
<i>♪ I always have and I always will ♪</i>

50:49.421 --> 50:50.797
Yeah, it's coke.

50:54.718 --> 50:56.970
You ever tried it before?
I've got some more.

50:58.221 --> 50:59.264
No, thank you.

51:00.807 --> 51:04.478
I offered to help the maids
prepare the study.

51:05.228 --> 51:06.229
Your grandfa...

51:06.313 --> 51:09.733
I'm sure you've had it before.
You're a city girl. You're all fancy.

51:10.609 --> 51:14.196
Your grandfather plans
to receive some old friends tomorrow.

51:14.279 --> 51:16.823
Well, let's hope they don't notice
the missing bourbon.

51:19.284 --> 51:20.284
Cheers.

51:22.537 --> 51:25.332
You look tired.
Perhaps you should get some sleep.

51:25.415 --> 51:27.751
He's a piece of work, my grandfather,
isn't he?

51:28.960 --> 51:29.960
He's...

51:31.379 --> 51:33.381
an interesting man.

51:35.133 --> 51:36.133
He's a...

51:37.010 --> 51:40.388
racist, homophobic, angry piece of shit.

51:46.103 --> 51:47.604
My dad bought a new house.

51:49.397 --> 51:51.983
Same fucking neighborhood as the old one.

51:53.527 --> 51:56.446
Not the big colonial on Summit,
it turns out, but...

51:57.322 --> 51:58.907
somewhere in that neighborhood.

51:59.241 --> 52:01.535
Asshole abandoned his family,

52:01.618 --> 52:04.162
didn't even have the decency
to move to another fucking town.

52:04.246 --> 52:07.415
Maybe he wants to continue
to be a part of your life.

52:09.918 --> 52:10.918
No.

52:18.051 --> 52:19.177
I look at him

52:19.261 --> 52:23.181
and I look at my grandfather,
and I think, "Where the hell do I end up?"

52:23.974 --> 52:26.226
Wherever you want, I think.

52:27.352 --> 52:28.352
Do you?

52:29.938 --> 52:31.815
Did you end up where you want to be?

52:32.399 --> 52:34.818
Cleaning up coke for a rich white kid.

52:35.527 --> 52:39.573
I'm helping my mother, so,
I'm exactly where I want to be.

52:40.073 --> 52:42.284
Well, fucking good for you.

52:45.162 --> 52:46.872
Fucking good for you!

52:49.124 --> 52:51.960
- Bryce! That's quite enough.
- Hey, Mom.

52:53.378 --> 52:55.088
Go to your room. Now!

52:56.631 --> 52:57.799
Guess I'm in trouble.

52:59.217 --> 53:00.218
Good night, Ani.

53:00.969 --> 53:02.512
I'm sorry about the mess.

53:04.681 --> 53:08.059
You are never to speak to her again.
You are not to go near her.

53:08.143 --> 53:10.645
Or you will have no home here,
do you understand me?

53:10.729 --> 53:13.481
- Understand?
- Yes. Yeah, I understand.

53:20.530 --> 53:23.533
I'm so sorry, Mrs. Walker.

53:24.034 --> 53:26.912
Don't be. You did nothing wrong.

53:26.995 --> 53:29.998
He was tired and upset about his father.

53:30.081 --> 53:33.084
Yes, there are all manner of excuses.

53:34.586 --> 53:35.587
But my son...

53:41.843 --> 53:43.303
You should be very careful.

53:53.355 --> 53:55.690
<i>That's why I think
it must be hard to be a boy.</i>

53:57.317 --> 53:59.611
<i>Because they still have no idea
what a man is.</i>

54:01.696 --> 54:03.949
- Is that comfortable?
- It's fine!

54:04.491 --> 54:05.491
Fine.

54:10.789 --> 54:11.789
Is he awake?

54:12.207 --> 54:14.918
Yes, but he's just taken his medicine.

54:15.794 --> 54:16.795
Excuse me.

54:17.837 --> 54:18.837
Stay.

54:19.089 --> 54:20.089
Please.

54:21.049 --> 54:22.550
This will only take a moment.

54:28.598 --> 54:29.766
Father...

54:40.318 --> 54:41.318
Harrison...

54:44.197 --> 54:45.991
I'm afraid your grandson is dead.

54:47.492 --> 54:49.369
We're attending his funeral tomorrow.

54:51.121 --> 54:52.122
My grandson?

54:53.581 --> 54:54.749
Bryce.

54:55.625 --> 54:56.710
Is dead?

54:57.419 --> 54:58.419
Yes.

55:00.964 --> 55:01.964
What the...

55:03.258 --> 55:05.593
What the hell happened?
What have you done?

55:05.677 --> 55:06.845
Where's Bryce?

55:07.637 --> 55:10.265
He's with the mortician,
being prepared for tomorrow.

55:10.348 --> 55:12.267
What have you done to him?

55:12.642 --> 55:14.019
Dad, please, lie down.

55:14.102 --> 55:16.938
Get the fuck out of my way,
I need to see my grandson!

55:17.022 --> 55:19.065
Where's my cane? Bryce!

55:19.149 --> 55:20.942
Get me my cane, God damn it.

55:21.026 --> 55:23.254
- I need my cane.
- You are not to stand. Doctor's orders.

55:23.278 --> 55:24.279
Where's my cane?

55:24.362 --> 55:27.282
Perhaps if you get him his cane
it will help calm him down.

55:27.365 --> 55:29.826
I had the maid store it
in the carriage house.

55:29.909 --> 55:30.910
Amorowat!

55:39.586 --> 55:41.087
<i>Men and their rage...</i>

55:42.839 --> 55:44.299
<i>and their insecurities,</i>

55:45.050 --> 55:46.051
<i>their fears...</i>

55:47.844 --> 55:50.597
<i>and all the things they do
to keep those hidden away.</i>

56:00.565 --> 56:01.566
Wow.

56:09.866 --> 56:13.119
We're sending you back to the future!

56:28.927 --> 56:30.053
<i>Alex was right.</i>

56:31.805 --> 56:32.806
<i>Nobody's clean.</i>

56:38.937 --> 56:39.979
